Text:
@whitee_rabbit - The Ocean's Trilogy probably won't happen. Sorry.

@lilsean23 - I hate to disappoint but I won't do subs for other languages. Everything about subs is too time consuming (making sure the timing is correct, whether it's a true translation or not, and finding/waiting for good ones to be available, or having to OCR them myself).

I ask that those who need other subs -- I've got requests for other languages, besides Spanish, on a different site -- add the SRT files themselves. You can use YAMB on a PC and Subler on a Mac, and there are google-able instructions. It's basically re-saving file -- NOT re-encoding -- so it takes very little time or CPU power. You just need (temporary) hard drive space.

@justneustis - you're very welcome. I'll call on you for encoding help when the time comes :)

@VladDj123 - If you mean Batman Begins & The Dark Knight, I will (hopefully) do those in July, before The Dark Knight Rises is in theaters.

@portydert - Not really a forced track, per se, but yes AppleTV & iTunes can be set to display a sub track by default, allowing you to set the BD's forced track as the first sub track. Sadly, I only know one person (offline, that is) whom I share movies with that chooses to do this besides me. Most of the other peeps I share movies offline with prefer to keep subs off, so it's up to them to know when to turn it on.

And there is no equivalent option for iPads, iPhones or iTouches (those only have default On/Off setting for closed captioning tracks, not subs).

So, it's just simpler for me to burn them in when it's an English film with a smattering of subs. (If this was, say, Pan's Labyrinth or Brotherhood of the Wolf, I wouldn't burn-in the subs).

@portydert - I'm very picky myself (I hope that shows ;) ) so you're only asking the questions I'd be asking if our roles were reversed. No worries man. :)

@nextgenex - You're very welcome!

@PatrickDevaney - tho I wouldn't expect it for a few months, when The Avengers is made available online, I'll most def encode in 1080p & 720p
